<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Centromadia</i> <i>pungens</i> and/or another <i>Centromadia</i> species is conspicuous to dominant in the herbaceous layer with <i>Atriplex</i> spp., <i>Bromus</i> spp., <i>Deschampsia</i> <i>danthonioides</i>, <i>Downingia</i> <i>bella</i>, <i>Erodium</i> <i>cicutarium</i>, <i>Frankenia</i> <i>salina</i>, <i>Hirschfeldia</i> <i>incana</i>, <i>Hordeum</i> <i>murinum</i>, <i>Lasthenia</i> <i>californica</i>, <i>Lasthenia</i> <i>fremontii</i>, <i>Trifolium</i> <i>depauperatum</i> and <i>Trifolium</i> <i>variegatum</i>. Emergent shrubs may be present at low cover, including <i>Suaeda</i> <i>moquinii</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 1 m; cover is intermittent. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Centromadia pungens</i> > 30% relative cover in the herbaceous layer (Klein and Evens 2005).</li>
		
		<li><i>Centromadia pungens, Deschampsia danthonioides, Trifolium</i> spp., <i>Phalaris lemmonii, Medicago polymorpha,</i> and <i>Downingia bella</i> present in the herbaceous layer (Barbour et al. 2007).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Vernally wet habitats, including edges of alkaline pools, bottoms of shallow pools, and alkaline flats with periodic or intermittent inundation. Soils are fine-textured alluvium, sometimes underlain by claypan or another impervious layer, poorly drained. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Centromadia (Hemizonia) pungens</i> as a FAC plant and other <i>Centromadia</i> spp. as FAC or FACU plants. </div>
</div>

        
